column12: Measurement condition : Vegetation; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: Open channel with significant vegetation
column14: FT2 boot wade just above riffle upstream of gauge, water level is low. Channel narrow, minimum spacing measurement, gravel bar in middle of riffle restricting majority of flow to edges. Significant vegetation growth in channel already, lots of algae. SNR variations at edges due to vegetation. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ DWL at arrival found reset, assumed to be due to anchor ice releasing, logger reset, did not take until 10:45. Strong upstream wind causing small surge. Significant vegetation growth in gauge pool already. Mid-section
GC: 0.000 HG: 0.588 Surge: 0.003  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  DWL

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , No Precipitation , Moderate Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: Thin layer of surface ice, with anchor ice below water.
column14: Trickle flow through riffle above gauge pool, no ice present at this section. Measured just below riffle. FT2 boot wade. Uneven panel spacing due to rocks obstructing flow, and less than 22 panels due to narrow section and shallow water depth. Used measurement for estimated flow. Attached summary file from measurement to .zip package, did not attach measurement file, just using as estimate. Clear ice, can see ice is frozen to bottom / sensor is in ice. OTT frozen in to anchor ice on bottom of channel. No water under ice. Took DWL for water over ice, did NOT reset logger due to frozen sensor. Do not apply SRC. Stage record invalid. Took second DWL after measurement for MGH, stage stable. Other Methods Estimated

column12: Measurement condition : Altered; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Ice jam below gauge pool. Open water at gauge pool and upstream.
column14: FT2 wading measurement taken 30m upstream of gauge, to keep away from backwater being created by ice jam at gauge. Measurement used minimum spacing, and had a 10% panel as a result. The measurement had several velocity angles, standard error warnings,and boundary interferencedue to floating ice pans, vegetation on the edges, and spacing. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Stage dropping significantly at visit. Multiple large ice jams in river causing backwater. One ice jam directly in gauge pool with water flowing over and under ice. Sensor not reset at first DWL as ice jam was shifting in chanel at the time. Second DWL taken after moving ice jam settled and found no SRC. Third DWL taken after measurement to confirm stable DWL and get accurate MGH. Small SRC found but no reset applied as water level is changing rapidly. Cut on stadia rod is dropping quickly between DWLs. Gauge pool too deep to check orifice, assumed to be stable / anchored. No SRC should be applied back / EST SRC possible. Initial SRC likely due to rapidly changing water level due to ice jam movement. Mid-section
GC: 0.000 HG: 0.708 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Vegetation; Smokey , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: Lots of vegetation on control and throughout the creek.
column14: Poor quality measurement, flow is an estimate based on measurement. Measured at gauge, heavy vegetation in channel, least vegetation at gauge. Many errors due to low flows and interference from vegetation. Very high downstream wind was causing surface water and vegetation to move downstream; when wind died down no flow visible. Backwater from vegetation slowed discharge. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ DWL from primary, large vegetation growth in channel.  Mid-section
GC: 0.000 HG: 0.597 Found (FD)
